{"sdkVersions":{"surrealdb":"v3.2.0",".net":"0.10.2","php":"2.0.0-alpha.1","javascript":"2.0.4","python":"2.0.0","rust":"unknown","golang":"v1.5.0","java":"1.0.0-beta.1"},"pageId":"\\/src\\/pages\\/learn\\/data-models","routeParams":{},"data":{"ast":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"heading","depth":2,"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Vector search vs full-text search"}],"id":"vector-search-vs-full-text-search"},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"SurrealDB supports "},{"type":"link","url":"\\/docs\\/learn\\/data-models\\/full-text-search\\/overview","title":"!undefined","children":[{"type":"text","value":"full-text search"}]},{"type":"text","value":" and Vector Search. Full-text search (FTS) involves indexing documents using an "},{"type":"link","url":"\\/docs\\/reference\\/query-language\\/statements\\/define\\/indexes#full-text-search-fulltext-index","title":"!undefined","children":[{"type":"text","value":"FTS index"}]},{"type":"text","value":" that makes use of an "},{"type":"link","url":"\\/docs\\/reference\\/query-language\\/statements\\/define\\/analyzer","title":"!undefined","children":[{"type":"text","value":"analyzer"}]},{"type":"text","value":" that breaks down text using "},{"type":"link","url":"\\/docs\\/reference\\/query-language\\/statements\\/define\\/analyzer#tokenizers","title":"!undefined","children":[{"type":"text","value":"tokenizers"}]},{"type":"text","value":" and "},{"type":"link","url":"\\/docs\\/reference\\/query-language\\/statements\\/define\\/analyzer#filters","title":"!undefined","children":[{"type":"text","value":"filters"}]},{"type":"text","value":"."}]},{"type":"image","src":"\\/docs\\/assets\\/static\\/lead.BEMc22N4.png","alt":"Google search for the word 'lead'"},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"The image above is a Google search for the word “lead”, a word with more than one definition (and pronunciation!). Lead can mean 'taking initiative', as well as the chemical element with the symbol 'Pb'."}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Let's consider this in the context of a database of liquid samples which note down harmful chemicals that are found in them."}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"In the example below, we have a table called "},{"type":"inlineCode","value":"liquids"},{"type":"text","value":" with a "},{"type":"inlineCode","value":"sample"},{"type":"text","value":" field and a "},{"type":"inlineCode","value":"content"},{"type":"text","value":" field.  Next, we can define a "},{"type":"link","url":"\\/docs\\/reference\\/query-language\\/statements\\/define\\/indexes#full-text-search-index","title":"!undefined","children":[{"type":"text","value":"full-text index"}]},{"type":"text","value":" on the "},{"type":"inlineCode","value":"content"},{"type":"text","value":" field by first defining an analyzer called "},{"type":"inlineCode","value":"liquid_analyzer"},{"type":"text","value":". We can then "},{"type":"link","url":"\\/docs\\/reference\\/query-language\\/statements\\/define\\/indexes","title":"!undefined","children":[{"type":"text","value":"define an index"}]},{"type":"text","value":" on the content field in the liquid table and set our "},{"type":"link","url":"\\/docs\\/reference\\/query-language\\/statements\\/define\\/analyzer","title":"!undefined","children":[{"type":"text","value":"custom analyzer"}]},{"type":"text","value":" ("},{"type":"inlineCode","value":"liquid_analyzer"},{"type":"text","value":")to search through the index."}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Then, using the select statement to retrieve all the samples containing the chemical lead will also bring up samples that mention the word "},{"type":"inlineCode","value":"lead"},{"type":"text","value":"."}]},{"type":"jsxComponent","name":"SurrealistMini","attributes":{"url":"https:\\/\\/app.surrealdb.com\\/mini?query=--+Insert+a+sample+%26+content+field+into+a+liquids+table%0A%0AINSERT+INTO+liquids+%5B%0A++++%7Bsample%3A%27Sea+water%27%2C+content%3A+%27The+sea+water+contains+some+amount+of+lead%27%7D%2C%0A++++%7Bsample%3A%27Tap+water%27%2C+content%3A+%27The+team+lead+by+Dr.+Rose+found+out+that+the+tap+water+in+was+potable%27%7D%2C%0A++++%7Bsample%3A%27Sewage+water%27%2C+content%3A+%27High+amounts+of+a+were+found+in+Sewage+water%27%7D%0A%5D%3B%0A%0A--+Define+an+analyzer+for+the+liquid+table+and+an+index+on+the+content+field+with+the+analyzer%0A%0ADEFINE+ANALYZER+liquid_analyzer+TOKENIZERS+blank%2Cclass%2Ccamel%2Cpunct+FILTERS+snowball%28english%29%3B%0ADEFINE+INDEX+liquid_content+ON+liquids+FIELDS+content+SEARCH+ANALYZER+liquid_analyzer+BM25+HIGHLIGHTS%3B%0A%0A--+Retrieve+all+the+samples+containing+the+chemical+lead+will+also+bring+up+samples+that+simply+mention+the+word+lead%0A%0ASELECT%0A++sample%2C%0A++content%0AFROM+liquids%0AWHERE+content+%400%40+%27lead%27%3B&orientation=horizontal"},"children":[],"position":{"start":18,"end":18}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"If you read through the content of the tap water sample, you’ll notice that it does not contain any lead in it but it has the mention of the word "},{"type":"inlineCode","value":"lead"},{"type":"text","value":" under “The team lead by Dr. Rose…” which means that the team was guided by Dr. Rose."}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"The search pulled up both the records although the tap water sample had no lead in it. This example shows us that while full-text search does a great job at matching query terms with indexed documents, on its own it may not be the best solution for use cases where the query terms have deeper context and scope for ambiguity."}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"For vector-side retrieval on the same story, see "},{"type":"link","url":"\\/docs\\/learn\\/data-models\\/vector-search\\/similarity-search","title":"!undefined","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Similarity search"}]},{"type":"text","value":"."}]},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Hybrid search functions"}],"id":"hybrid-search-functions"},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"As mentioned above, full-text search and vector search can both be used in SurrealDB. In addition, some functions exist inside the "},{"type":"link","url":"\\/docs\\/reference\\/query-language\\/functions\\/database-functions\\/search","title":"!undefined","children":[{"type":"inlineCode","value":"search::"}]},{"type":"text","value":" namespace that take both full-text and vector arguments in order to produce a single unified output."}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Here is an example of one of them called "},{"type":"link","url":"\\/docs\\/reference\\/query-language\\/functions\\/database-functions\\/search#searchrrf","title":"!undefined","children":[{"type":"inlineCode","value":"search::rrf()"}]},{"type":"text","value":" which does this using an algorithm called reciprocal rank fusion."}]},{"type":"code","value":"-- Sample data --\nCREATE test:1 SET text = \"Graph databases are great.\", embedding = [0.10, 0.20, 0.30];\nCREATE test:2 SET text = \"Relational databases store tables.\", embedding = [0.05, 0.10, 0.00];\nCREATE test:3 SET text = \"This document mentions graphs.\", embedding = [0.20, 0.10, 0.25];\n\n-- Analyzer used by the full‑text index\nDEFINE ANALYZER simple TOKENIZERS class, punct FILTERS lowercase, ascii;\n\n-- Full‑text index\nDEFINE INDEX idx_text\n  ON TABLE test FIELDS text FULLTEXT ANALYZER simple BM25;","lang":"surql"},{"type":"jsxComponent","name":"Tabs","attributes":{"synckey":"hybrid-vector-index"},"children":[{"type":"jsxComponent","name":"TabItem","attributes":{"label":"HNSW (in-memory)"},"children":[{"type":"code","value":"DEFINE INDEX idx_embedding\n    ON TABLE test \n    FIELDS embedding \n    HNSW DIMENSION 3 DIST COSINE;","lang":"surql"}],"position":{"start":1,"end":10}},{"type":"jsxComponent","name":"TabItem","attributes":{"label":"DISKANN (on-disk)"},"children":[{"type":"jsxComponent","name":"Since","attributes":{"v":"v3.1.0"},"children":[],"position":{"start":2,"end":2}},{"type":"code","value":"DEFINE INDEX idx_embedding\n    ON TABLE test \n    FIELDS embedding \n    DISKANN DIMENSION 3 DIST COSINE TYPE F32;","lang":"surql"},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"For very large embedding sets that do not fit comfortably in RAM, prefer DISKANN. It is "},{"type":"strong","children":[{"type":"text","value":"not available on WASM"}]},{"type":"text","value":" builds."}]}],"position":{"start":11,"end":24}}],"position":{"start":46,"end":71}},{"type":"code","value":"-- Query vector (whatever your embedding model produced for \"graph databases\")\nLET $qvec = [0.12, 0.18, 0.27];\n\n-- Vector search: top 2 nearest neighbours\nLET $vs = SELECT id FROM test  WHERE embedding \u003c|2,100|> $qvec;\n\n-- Full‑text search: top 2 lexical matches\nLET $ft = SELECT id, search::score(1) as score FROM test\n          WHERE text @1@ 'graph' ORDER BY score DESC LIMIT 2;\n\n-- Fuse with Reciprocal Rank Fusion (k defaults to 60 if omitted)\nsearch::rrf([$vs, $ft], 2, 60);","lang":"surql"}]},"headings":[{"id":"vector-search-vs-full-text-search","text":"Vector search vs full-text search","depth":2},{"id":"hybrid-search-functions","text":"Hybrid search functions","depth":2}],"navigation":[{"title":"Overview","icon":"!undefined","links":[{"title":"Data Models","path":"\\/learn\\/data-models"}]},{"title":"Document","icon":"!undefined","links":[{"title":"Document model","path":"\\/learn\\/data-models\\/document\\/overview"},{"title":"Nested objects and arrays","path":"\\/learn\\/data-models\\/document\\/nested-objects-and-arrays"},{"title":"Schema modes","path":"\\/learn\\/data-models\\/document\\/schema-modes"},{"title":"Common patterns","path":"\\/learn\\/data-models\\/document\\/common-patterns"}]},{"title":"Graph","icon":"!undefined","links":[{"title":"Graph model","path":"\\/learn\\/data-models\\/graph\\/overview"},{"title":"Creating relations","path":"\\/learn\\/data-models\\/graph\\/creating-relations"},{"title":"Graph traversal","path":"\\/learn\\/data-models\\/graph\\/graph-traversal"},{"title":"Recursive traversals","path":"\\/learn\\/data-models\\/graph\\/recursive-traversals"},{"title":"Record links vs graph relations","path":"\\/learn\\/data-models\\/graph\\/record-links-vs-graph-relations"},{"title":"Social network patterns","path":"\\/learn\\/data-models\\/graph\\/social-network-patterns"},{"title":"Knowledge graph patterns","path":"\\/learn\\/data-models\\/graph\\/knowledge-graph-patterns"}]},{"title":"Full-text search","icon":"!undefined","links":[{"title":"Full-text search model","path":"\\/learn\\/data-models\\/full-text-search\\/overview"},{"title":"Analyzers and tokenizers","path":"\\/learn\\/data-models\\/full-text-search\\/analyzers-and-tokenizers"},{"title":"Search indexes","path":"\\/learn\\/data-models\\/full-text-search\\/search-indexes"},{"title":"Scoring and ranking","path":"\\/learn\\/data-models\\/full-text-search\\/scoring-and-ranking"},{"title":"Other ways to work with text","path":"\\/learn\\/data-models\\/full-text-search\\/other-ways-to-work-with-text"}]},{"title":"Vector search","icon":"!undefined","links":[{"title":"Vector search model","path":"\\/learn\\/data-models\\/vector-search\\/overview"},{"title":"Hybrid search","path":"\\/learn\\/data-models\\/vector-search\\/hybrid-search"},{"title":"Similarity search","path":"\\/learn\\/data-models\\/vector-search\\/similarity-search"},{"title":"Vector indexes","path":"\\/learn\\/data-models\\/vector-search\\/vector-indexes"},{"title":"RAG architecture patterns","path":"\\/learn\\/data-models\\/vector-search\\/rag-architecture-patterns"},{"title":"Embedding pipelines","path":"\\/learn\\/data-models\\/vector-search\\/embedding-pipelines"}]},{"title":"Geospatial","icon":"!undefined","links":[{"title":"Geospatial model","path":"\\/learn\\/data-models\\/geospatial\\/overview"},{"title":"Geometry types","path":"\\/learn\\/data-models\\/geospatial\\/geometry-types"},{"title":"Spatial queries","path":"\\/learn\\/data-models\\/geospatial\\/spatial-queries"},{"title":"Distance and proximity","path":"\\/learn\\/data-models\\/geospatial\\/distance-and-proximity"},{"title":"Location-based patterns","path":"\\/learn\\/data-models\\/geospatial\\/location-based-patterns"}]},{"title":"Time-series","icon":"!undefined","links":[{"title":"Time-series model","path":"\\/learn\\/data-models\\/time-series\\/overview"},{"title":"Using SurrealDB as a time series database","path":"\\/learn\\/data-models\\/time-series\\/using-as-time-series-database"},{"title":"Time buckets and windowing","path":"\\/learn\\/data-models\\/time-series\\/time-buckets-and-windowing"},{"title":"Aggregation queries","path":"\\/learn\\/data-models\\/time-series\\/aggregation-queries"},{"title":"IoT and telemetry patterns","path":"\\/learn\\/data-models\\/time-series\\/iot-and-telemetry-patterns"}]}],"contentPath":"learn\\/data-models\\/vector-search\\/hybrid-search.mdx","breadcrumbs":["Vector search"],"title":"Hybrid search","description":"Compare lexical full-text search with vector similarity on the same dataset and fuse rankings with search::rrf and related helpers."}}
